def: A verse containing eight feet; as, --Deep'' in|to'' the | dark''ness | peer''ing, | long'' I | stood''there | wond'''ring, | fear''ing. Poe.
The quality or state of being invisible; invisibility.
An inferior kind of veneration or worship, given to the angelsand saints as the servants of God.
In a straddling position; astride; bestriding; as, to sitastraddle a horse.
Deserving, disapprobation or blame.-- Dis`com*mend"a*ble*ness, n.
The fruit or berry of the Anamirta Cocculus, a climbing plantof the East Indies. It is a poisonous narcotic and stimulant.
